---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro'
import BackButton from '../../../components/BackButton.astro'
import DescriptionCard from '../../../components/DescriptionCard.astro'
import CodePreviewCard from '../../../components/CodePreviewCard.astro'
import DescriptionCardHeader from '../../../components/DescriptionCardHeader.astro'
import DescriptionCardText from '../../../components/DescriptionCardText.astro'
import DescriptionCardExampleLink from '../../../components/DescriptionCardExampleLink.astro'
import TopicPageNavbar from '../../../components/TopicPageNavbar.astro'
---

<Layout title="JS Cheat Sheet | Randomness">
    <TopicPageNavbar>
        <h1 class="logo">
            <span>JS</span> Cheat Sheet
        </h1>
        <BackButton className="back-button" id="back_button" href="/first_semester/" buttonText="Back to overview"/>    </TopicPageNavbar>    
    <div class="container desc-container">
        <DescriptionCard class="card what-card">
            <div class="card what-card">
                <DescriptionCardHeader class="what-header" headerText="Randomness" />

                <DescriptionCardText>
                    Randomness is used in many cases. You use it in your game, but that's just one of an unlimited amount of use cases. It's being used, when you want to let the computer take over the control of a certain action, and you typically want something to happen based on an outcome randomly generated by the computer.
                </DescriptionCardText>
            </div>
        </DescriptionCard>

        <DescriptionCard class="card syntax-card">
            <div class="card syntax-card">
                <DescriptionCardHeader class="syntax-header" headerText="Syntax" />

                <DescriptionCardText>
                    To generate a random number in JavaScript, the <span class="method">method</span> <span class="object">Math</span><span class="method">.random</span><span class="parentheses">()</span> is being used. This <span class="method">method</span> generates a random decimal number between 0 and 1 (0 <b><em>inclusive</em></b> and 1 <b><em>excluded</em></b>). 
                    To generate a random number between 1 and a higher value, and how to turn the number into a whole number, see the example <DescriptionCardExampleLink href="https://codepen.io/Schweitz/pen/GRbpNbJ" linkText="here." target="_blank" />
                </DescriptionCardText>
            </div>
    </div>
</Layout>